// licenses.proto defines the BPP license-lifecycle surface for ZyINS
// (signup, activation, validation, lock/unlock, refresh, deactivate).
//
// Two surfaces coexist and this file covers both:
//
//   1. Legacy `/v1/licenses/*` endpoints — server-to-server, deprecated.
//      They take credentials in the request body, accept Bearer or
//      ServiceToken auth, and are being sunset per ADR-023.
//
//   2. Singular `/v1/license/*` endpoints (ADR-013) — authenticated-self.
//      The caller is identified by the auth context (LicenseAuth header
//      + X-Device-ID + X-Device-Signature); the body carries no
//      credentials. Phase 2 of the BPP migration moves clients here
//      and adds LicenseHMAC (ADR-018) as the preferred credential.
